.RE

ErlNifMonitor
.RS 2
This is an opaque data type that identifies a monitor.

.PP
The nif writer is to provide the memory for storing the monitor when calling \fIenif_monitor_process\fR. The address of the data is not stored by the runtime system, so \fIErlNifMonitor\fR can be used as any other data, it can be copied, moved in memory, forgotten, and so on. To compare two monitors, \fIenif_compare_monitors\fR must be used.


