.SS "enif_release_resource()"

.IP
.nf
void enif_release_resource(
        void* obj);

.fi

.PP
Removes a reference to resource object \fIobj\fR obtained from \fIenif_alloc_resource\fR. The resource object is destructed when the last reference is removed. Each call to \fIenif_release_resource\fR must correspond to a previous call to \fIenif_alloc_resource\fR or \fIenif_keep_resource\fR. References made by \fIenif_make_resource\fR can only be removed by the garbage collector.

.PP
There are no guarantees exactly when the destructor of an unreferenced resource is called. It could be called directly by \fIenif_release_resource\fR but it could also be scheduled to be called at a later time possibly by another thread.

.PP
Available since OTP R13B04

