.SS "enif_whereis_pid()"

.IP
.nf
int enif_whereis_pid(
        ErlNifEnv *caller_env,
        ERL_NIF_TERM name,
        ErlNifPid *pid);

.fi

.PP
Looks up a process by its registered name.

caller_env
.RS 2
The environment of the calling thread (process bound or callback environment) or 
\fINULL\fR if calling from a custom thread not spawned by ERTS.

.RE

name
.RS 2
The name of a registered process, as an atom.


.RE

*pid
.RS 2
The 
\fIErlNifPid\fR in which the resolved process id is stored.

.RE

.PP
On success, sets \fI*pid\fR to the local process registered with \fIname\fR and returns \fItrue\fR. If \fIname\fR is not a registered process, or is not an atom, \fIfalse\fR is returned and \fI*pid\fR is unchanged.

.PP
Works as \fIerlang:whereis/1\fR, but restricted to processes. See \fIenif_whereis_port\fR to resolve registered ports.

.PP
Available since OTP 20.0

.SS "enif_whereis_port()"

.IP
.nf
int enif_whereis_port(
        ErlNifEnv *caller_env,
        ERL_NIF_TERM name,
        ErlNifPort *port);

.fi

.PP
Looks up a port by its registered name.

caller_env
.RS 2
The environment of the calling thread (process bound or callback environment) or 
\fINULL\fR if calling from a custom thread not spawned by ERTS.

.RE

name
.RS 2
The name of a registered port, as an atom.


.RE

*port
.RS 2
The 
\fIErlNifPort\fR in which the resolved port id is stored.

.RE

.PP
On success, sets \fI*port\fR to the port registered with \fIname\fR and returns \fItrue\fR. If \fIname\fR is not a registered port, or is not an atom, \fIfalse\fR is returned and \fI*port\fR is unchanged.

.PP
Works as \fIerlang:whereis/1\fR, but restricted to ports. See \fIenif_whereis_pid\fR to resolve registered processes.

.PP
Available since OTP 20.0

